{"id":842,"date":"2015-06-08T13:02:39","date_gmt":"2015-06-08T17:02:39","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/?p=842"},"modified":"2017-05-23T12:36:48","modified_gmt":"2017-05-23T16:36:48","slug":"new-msu-extension-bulletin-minimizing-pesticide-risk-to-bees-in-fruit-crops","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/new-msu-extension-bulletin-minimizing-pesticide-risk-to-bees-in-fruit-crops\/","title":{"rendered":"New MSU Extension Bulletin: Minimizing Pesticide Risk to Bees in Fruit Crops"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"fcbkbttn_buttons_block\" id=\"fcbkbttn_left\"><\/div><p><a href=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/new-msu-extension-bulletin-minimizing-pesticide-risk-to-bees-in-fruit-crops\/msu-extension-bulletin\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-843\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-843\" src=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/MSU-Extension-bulletin-1024x598.png\" alt=\"MSU Extension bulletin\" width=\"700\" height=\"409\" srcset=\"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/MSU-Extension-bulletin-1024x598.png 1024w, https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/MSU-Extension-bulletin-300x175.png 300w, https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/MSU-Extension-bulletin-768x448.png 768w, https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/MSU-Extension-bulletin.png 1538w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Project ICP partners\u00a0Emily May, Rufus Isaacs, and Julianna Wilson (Michigan State University), have authored a\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/msue.anr.msu.edu\/\" target=\"_blank\">Michigan State University Extension<\/a>\u00a0guide,\u00a0\u201c<a href=\"http:\/\/msue.anr.msu.edu\/uploads\/236\/68700\/E-3245.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Minimizing Pesticide Risk to Bees in Fruit Crops<\/a>,\u201d which\u00a0outlines pesticide risks to bees on fruit farms and suggests\u00a0best management\u00a0strategies to\u00a0minimize these risks. The document includes\u00a0toxicity ranking tables for insecticides and fungicides registered in Michigan fruit crops\u00a0to allow growers, extension educators and crop consultants to make informed decisions about pest management and bee protection.<\/p>\n<p>Suggested best management practices for minimizing pesticide risk to bees include:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Develop and implement a pollination contract with your beekeeper.<\/li>\n<li>Use integrated pest management (<abbr title=\"Integrated Pest Management\">IPM<\/abbr>) to reduce the need for sprays.<\/li>\n<li>Avoid pesticide sprays during crop bloom.<\/li>\n<li>Apply pesticides after sunset or before sunrise, or when air temperature is below 50 degrees Fahrenheit.<\/li>\n<li>Select the least toxic pesticides and formulations when possible.<\/li>\n<li>Reduce drift onto areas outside crop fields.<\/li>\n<li>Remove flowering weeds from crops before spraying.<\/li>\n<li>Provide bee-friendly habitat away from crops.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>The guide is available from <abbr title=\"Michigan State University\">MSU<\/abbr> Extension <a href=\"http:\/\/msue.anr.msu.edu\/uploads\/236\/68700\/E-3245.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Project ICP partners\u00a0Emily May, Rufus Isaacs, and Julianna Wilson (Michigan State University), have authored a\u00a0Michigan State University Extension\u00a0guide,\u00a0\u201cMinimizing Pesticide Risk to Bees in Fruit Crops,\u201d which\u00a0outlines pesticide risks to bees on fruit farms and suggests\u00a0best management\u00a0strategies to\u00a0minimize these risks. The&hellip; <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":843,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_exactmetrics_skip_tracking":false,"_exactmetrics_sitenote_active":false,"_exactmetrics_sitenote_note":"","_exactmetrics_sitenote_category":0,"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":true,"_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id":0,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content":false,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":"","jetpack_publicize_message":"","jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled":true,"jetpack_social_post_already_shared":true,"jetpack_social_options":{"image_generator_settings":{"template":"highway","default_image_id":0,"font":"","enabled":false},"version":2}},"categories":[15],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-842","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-project-icp-extension"],"jetpack_publicize_connections":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/01\/MSU-Extension-bulletin.png","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p58KSL-dA","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/842","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=842"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/842\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":845,"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/842\/revisions\/845"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/843"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=842"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=842"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=842"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{re